# monday.com AI Platform Landing Pages ‚Äî Cursor Rules

## Shell Environment

- **Windows PowerShell** ‚Äî NEVER use `&&` to chain commands (use `;` or separate calls)
- No heredocs ‚Äî pass strings directly or use files
- Use `pnpm` as the package manager (not npm or yarn)

## Tech Stack Rules

- **React 18.3** ‚Äî functional components only, no class components
- **TypeScript strict** ‚Äî no `any` types unless absolutely unavoidable; prefer explicit interfaces
- **Tailwind CSS 4** via `@tailwindcss/vite` ‚Äî there is NO `tailwind.config.js`; all theme tokens live in `src/styles/theme.css` using `@theme inline`
- **motion/react** (Framer Motion) ‚Äî import from `motion/react`, not `framer-motion`
- **Path alias** ‚Äî use `@/` for imports from `src/` (e.g., `@/hooks/useSupabase`)
- **Supabase** ‚Äî client in `src/lib/supabase.ts`, all hooks in `src/hooks/useSupabase.ts`

## Naming Conventions

### Files & Directories

- **Components**: PascalCase with `.tsx` extension (e.g., `WorkManagementFirstFold.tsx`)
- **Data/utility files**: camelCase with `.ts` extension (e.g., `wmDepartmentData.ts`, `aiCompanies.ts`)
- **Hooks**: camelCase starting with `use` (e.g., `useSupabase.ts`)
- **Component directories**: camelCase matching the page area (e.g., `workManagement/`, `agents/`, `platform/`)
- **Page components**: PascalCase ending with `Page` or `App` (e.g., `WorkManagementLandingPage.tsx`, `AdminApp.tsx`)

### Code

- **Components**: PascalCase (`WorkManagementNav`, `ExecutionSystemSection`)
- **Hooks**: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useSiteSettings`, `useImageUpload`)
- **Interfaces/Types**: PascalCase (`SiteSettings`, `BoardItem`, `Department`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for static data arrays (`DEPARTMENTS`, `SQUAD_DEPARTMENTS`, `STATUS_CONFIG`)
- **Supabase keys**: Underscore-prefixed in DB (`_wm_dark_mode`), camelCase in TypeScript after hook parsing (`wm_dark_mode` ‚Üí read as `settings.wm_dark_mode`)
- **CSS variables**: Kebab-case with `--` prefix (`--color-brand-teal`, `--radius-lg`)
- **Event handlers**: `on` prefix for props (`onDeptChange`), `handle` prefix for internal (`handleClick`)

### Prefix Conventions

- `Wm` prefix for Work Management variants/types (`WmHeroLiveDelegation`, `WmFirstFoldVariant`)
- `agents_` prefix for Agents settings fields
- `wm_` prefix for Work Management settings fields
- `platform_` prefix for Platform settings fields

## Folder Structure Rules

```
src/app/components/{pageName}/     ‚Äî All components for a specific page
src/app/{PageName}LandingPage.tsx  ‚Äî Page assembly (composes sections in order)
src/admin/components/              ‚Äî All admin panel components
src/hooks/                         ‚Äî Shared hooks (keep useSupabase.ts as single source)
src/lib/                           ‚Äî Client libraries (Supabase, etc.)
src/styles/                        ‚Äî CSS files only (no JS config)
public/                            ‚Äî Static assets (logos, images, avatars)
public/logos/                      ‚Äî Company logo SVGs/PNGs
public/avatars/                    ‚Äî Person avatar images
public/department-avatars/         ‚Äî Department lead avatars
```

## Component Architecture Patterns

### Page Assembly Pattern

Each page has a single assembly file that composes section components in order:

```tsx
export default function WorkManagementLandingPage() {
  const { settings } = useSiteSettings();
  return (
    <div>
      <WorkManagementNav />
      <WorkManagementFirstFold />
      <WorkManagementPlatformLayers />
      {/* ...more sections */}
      <WorkManagementFooter />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Section Component Pattern

Each section is a self-contained component in its own file. It reads its own settings via `useSiteSettings()` and renders independently.

### Variant Pattern

Configurable sections use variant enums. The admin sets a variant string in Supabase; the component switches rendering:

```tsx
const { settings } = useSiteSettings();
switch (settings.wm_first_fold_variant) {
  case 'live_delegation': return <WmHeroLiveDelegation {...props} />;
  case 'cinematic_assembly': return <WmHeroCinematicAssembly {...props} />;
  default: return <DefaultHero {...props} />;
}
```

### Settings Flow

```
Admin saves ‚Üí Supabase site_settings.sections_visibility (underscore-prefixed keys)
  ‚Üí useSiteSettings() strips prefixes, merges defaults
    ‚Üí Component reads specific field ‚Üí conditional render
```

## Preferred Libraries

| Purpose | Library | Import |
|---------|---------|--------|
| Animation | motion | `from 'motion/react'` |
| Icons | lucide-react | `from 'lucide-react'` |
| UI primitives | Radix UI | `from '@radix-ui/react-*'` |
| Complex UI | MUI | `from '@mui/material'` (use sparingly) |
| Class merging | tailwind-merge + clsx | `cn()` utility |
| Toasts | sonner | `from 'sonner'` |
| Drag & drop | @dnd-kit | `from '@dnd-kit/core'` |
| Date utilities | date-fns | `from 'date-fns'` |
| Forms | react-hook-form | `from 'react-hook-form'` |
| Charts | recharts | `from 'recharts'` |
| Routing | react-router-dom | `from 'react-router-dom'` |
| Backend | @supabase/supabase-js | Via `@/lib/supabase` |

## Design Tokens

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| Brand teal | `#00D2D2` | CTAs, accents, highlights |
| Dark background | `#0a0a0a` | Page backgrounds |
| Card background | `#141414` | Card/panel fills |
| Card border | `#1e1e1e` | Card borders |
| Red | `#FF3D57` | Status dots, alerts |
| Yellow | `#FFCB00` | Status dots, warnings |
| Green | `#00D2D2` | Status dots, success |
| Blue | `#6161FF` | Status dots, info |
| Purple | `#A25DDC` | Status dots, special |

## Animation Guidelines

- Use `motion.div` (not `motion("div")`) for animated elements
- Prefer `AnimatePresence` for mount/unmount animations
- Use `whileInView` for scroll-triggered reveals
- Keep durations between 0.3s‚Äì0.8s for UI transitions
- Use `ease` or `[0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94]` for smooth easing
- Stagger children with `transition.staggerChildren`

## Supabase Rules

- All settings go through `useSiteSettings()` ‚Äî never query `site_settings` directly in components
- New settings: add key to `SiteSettings` interface in `useSupabase.ts`, add default value, add `_` prefixed key mapping
- Image uploads go to the `Vibe` storage bucket via `useImageUpload()`
- Design assets use `useDesignAssets(category)` hook

## Code Quality

- No comments that just narrate what code does
- No `console.log` in production code (remove after debugging)
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never use `var`
- Destructure props and hook returns
- Keep components under 400 lines; extract sub-components for large sections
- Use `key` props correctly in lists (never use array index as key for dynamic lists)

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT create a `tailwind.config.js` ‚Äî Tailwind 4 uses CSS-based config in `theme.css`
- Do NOT install `framer-motion` ‚Äî use `motion` package (import from `motion/react`)
- Do NOT use `npm` or `yarn` ‚Äî use `pnpm`
- Do NOT chain PowerShell commands with `&&` ‚Äî use `;` or separate lines
- Do NOT add new Supabase tables without updating `useSupabase.ts` hooks
- Do NOT use inline styles for colors that exist as design tokens
- Do NOT create separate CSS modules ‚Äî use Tailwind classes or `theme.css` variables
